</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="58" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="9" pageNumber="58">
Four species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Triploechus</taxonomicName>
are present in Nearctic region: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus luridus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luridus">Triploechus luridus</taxonomicName>
Hall, 1975; 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus novus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novus">Triploechus novus</taxonomicName>
(Williston, 1893); 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus sackeni" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sackeni">Triploechus sackeni</taxonomicName>
(Bigot, 1892); 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus stagei" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stagei">Triploechus stagei</taxonomicName>
Hall, 1975. Of these 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus stagei" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stagei">Triploechus stagei</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Mexico and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Triploechus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triploechus novus" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="novus">Triploechus novus</taxonomicName>
has the widest distribution of this genus, being present in the south of the USA and center of Mexico. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall, JC" editor="Griffiths, GCD" journalOrPublisher="E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart" pageId="29" pageNumber="78" pagination="97 - 184" title="Bombyliidae." url="10.1163/187631283x00100" volumeTitle="Flies of the Nearctic Region" year="1981">Hall and Evenhuis (1981)</bibRefCitation>
present a revision and key for species for this genus.
</paragraph>
